+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HZJT1hfHLMtV2u4x7Kuufu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture of all the bugs. Let me analyze and fix them systematically.\n\n**Bugs identified:**\n\n1. **EventBus global handlers** (`src/events/bus.ts`): Handlers use a module-level `globalHandlers` map shared across all instances. Tests create new `EventBus` instances in `beforeEach` but old handlers persist. Need instance-level handlers.\n\n2. **OrderRepository.update** (`src/orders/repository.ts:38`): `{ ...updates, id, updatedAt }` overwrites everything — doesn't merge with existing. Should be `{ ...existing, ...updates, id, updatedAt }`.\n\n3. **BillingService.handleRefund** (`src/billing/service.ts:25`): `handleRefund` isn't bound with `.bind(this)` — `this` is undefined when called as event handler.\n\n4. **calculateOrderTotal** (`src/billing/calculator.ts:23`): `total` isn't rounded — `afterDiscount + taxAmount` can produce floating-point imprecision. Need `Math.round(total * 100) / 100`.\n\n5. **OrderService.refundOrder** (`src/orders/service.ts:99`): `>=` should be `>` — day 30 should be allowed (test expects refund on exactly day 30).\n\n6. **InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled** (`src/inventory/service.ts:50`): Checks `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` but `cancelOrder` in `OrderService` doesn't include `status` in the emitted event — need to remove this check or add `status` to emitted event. Looking at the test (inventory.test.ts:73-78), the cancel event includes `status: 'cancelled'`. But `OrderService.cancelOrder` doesn't emit `status`. The issue is that this check prevents the handler from releasing stock when called from OrderService. Since the test for inventory directly emits with `status`, but the OrderService doesn't... Let me re-examine.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the test failures:\n- Inventory tests \"releases stock\" and \"concurrent orders\" fail with \"Insufficient stock for product SKU-1\" — this is because of the **global handlers** bug. When the second test runs, the handler from the first `beforeEach` still exists, so `handleOrderCreated` runs twice, trying to reserve stock twice.\n\nLet me fix all the bugs now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6361,"cache_read_input_tokens":31244,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6361},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8bff2ca8-e945-4b09-b3f5-d94c74c03c64","uuid":"0793a8d3-78ac-4d4d-97be-9c6a8b87d76b"}
